{
  "doc_id": "12312",
  "text": "In contrast to standardized language, UGC is often informal, with less adherence to conventions regarding punctuation, spelling, and style [CITATION_1] . Therefore, it is considerably noisy, containing ad-hoc abbreviations, phonetic substitutions, customized abbreviations, and slang language [CITATION_2] . Considering the specificity of such content, traditional techniques -such as lexiconbased substitution -are not capable to properly handle with many types of noise. Thus, in order to achieve satisfactory results, it is necessary to deeply analyze UGC and develop specific methods aimed at normalizing it.",
